</comment>
                            <comment id="14581917" author="cstein" created="Tue, 16 May 2023 07:27:41 -0700"  >Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/14015&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/14015&lt;/a&gt; as a proposal that gets rid of all direct `java.io.File` usages by introducing new constants in ToolBox, based on system property values.</comment>
                            <comment id="14581913" author="cstein" created="Tue, 16 May 2023 07:06:00 -0700"  >The command &amp;quot;grep -r java.io.File $(find test/langtools -name toolbox)&amp;quot; lists the following files:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;test/langtools/tools/lib/toolbox/JarTask.java:import java.io.File;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;test/langtools/tools/lib/toolbox/JavacTask.java:import java.io.File;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;test/langtools/tools/lib/toolbox/JavadocTask.java:import java.io.File;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;test/langtools/tools/lib/toolbox/AbstractTask.java:import java.io.File;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;test/langtools/tools/lib/toolbox/ModuleBuilder.java:import java.io.File;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
All usages of `java.io.File` are reasonable; mostly they use the `pathSeparator` constant field defined in the `File` class, and `AbstractTask` needs to pass `File` instance to the `ProcessBuilder` Redirect API.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The latter `new File(String)` occurances can be replaced by `Path.of(String).toFile()` for migration&amp;#39;s sake - but there&amp;#39;s not much to do about `java.io.File.pathSeparator`. Right?</comment>
